properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 8 at 2:21PM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...ACCUMULATING SNOW EXPECTED ON SUNDAY...

* WHAT...A period of moderate to heavy snow expected from mid
morning into the afternoon. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 8
inches.

* WHERE...Marquette, Green Lake and Sauk Counties.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Snow covered roads and limited visibility will create
difficult driving conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Be prepared to allow extra time to reach
your destination on Sunday.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
